            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
              <div class="bg-white rounded-[14px] p-4 border border-brand-teal/5"><p class="font-heading font-bold text-brand-teal text-sm mb-1">Client Summary</p><p class="text-xs text-brand-charcoal/60 leading-relaxed">HD type, authority, defined/open centers, elemental distribution, Ayurvedic constitution. The high-level architecture of the person's biopsychological structure.</p></div>
              <div class="bg-white rounded-[14px] p-4 border border-brand-teal/5"><p class="font-heading font-bold text-brand-teal text-sm mb-1">Armor Map</p><p class="text-xs text-brand-charcoal/60 leading-relaxed">7 Reichian character armor segments (Ocular through Pelvic) mapped to fascial patterns. Each rated Armored/Flexible with session numbers. Tells you WHERE the body holds its story.</p></div>
              <div class="bg-white rounded-[14px] p-4 border border-brand-teal/5"><p class="font-heading font-bold text-brand-teal text-sm mb-1">Polyvagal Guidance</p><p class="text-xs text-brand-charcoal/60 leading-relaxed">Nervous system profile: ventral capacity, sympathetic risk, dorsal shutdown risk. Pacing instructions, shutdown signs, whether verbal check-ins are reliable.</p></div>
              <div class="bg-white rounded-[14px] p-4 border border-brand-teal/5"><p class="font-heading font-bold text-brand-teal text-sm mb-1">Session Plan (10 Sessions)</p><p class="text-xs text-brand-charcoal/60 leading-relaxed">Per-session: Rolfing focus, armor priorities, chakra context, emotional release potential, pacing, schema therapy notes, structural friction.</p></div>
              <div class="bg-white rounded-[14px] p-4 border border-brand-teal/5"><p class="font-heading font-bold text-brand-teal text-sm mb-1">Gene Key Shadows</p><p class="text-xs text-brand-charcoal/60 leading-relaxed">64 Gene Keys mapped to body regions. Gates activated by planetary positions — each shadow names the fascial holding pattern the client's structure is organized around.</p></div>
              <div class="bg-white rounded-[14px] p-4 border border-brand-teal/5"><p class="font-heading font-bold text-brand-teal text-sm mb-1">Cosmobiology Friction</p><p class="text-xs text-brand-charcoal/60 leading-relaxed">Ebertin midpoint method: when two planets bisect a third, tension patterns emerge. Saturn midpoints = fascial restrictions. Mars = inflammatory patterns.</p></div>
              <div class="bg-white rounded-[14px] p-4 border border-brand-teal/5"><p class="font-heading font-bold text-brand-teal text-sm mb-1">Contraindications</p><p class="text-xs text-brand-charcoal/60 leading-relaxed">Safety flags from polyvagal risk scores, armor density, and HD open center vulnerability patterns. What to watch for, when to slow down.</p></div>
              <div class="bg-white rounded-[14px] p-4 border border-brand-teal/5"><p class="font-heading font-bold text-brand-teal text-sm mb-1">Practitioner Notes</p><p class="text-xs text-brand-charcoal/60 leading-relaxed">Saturn placement (fascial network tendency), gravitational baseline, open center field dynamics. Strategic guidance for working with THIS specific client.</p></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-brand-teal text-lg mb-2">How the Mapping Works</h3>
            <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-brand-charcoal/70 leading-relaxed">
              <p><strong>Planets → Body Regions.</strong> Each planet in a sign activates a specific body territory. Saturn in Scorpio = pelvic floor as structural anchor. Mars in Taurus = throat and neck as tension zones. The planetary ruler of each sign governs the anatomical territory.</p>
              <p><strong>HD Centers → Holding Patterns.</strong> Open centers absorb and amplify external energy. Over time this creates fascial holding: open Solar Plexus = braced diaphragm, open Root = hypertonic psoas, open Spleen = adhesed visceral ligaments. The armor map translates center mechanics into tissue predictions.</p>
              <p><strong>Gene Keys → Fascial Shadows.</strong> Each of the 64 Gene Keys has a Shadow (contracted expression) and a Gift (transformed). The Shadow name describes the fascial holding: Gate 33 (Forgetting) = anterior neck closure, Gate 21 (Control) = sternal armor, Gate 60 (Rigidity) = global superficial tension. Activated gates derived from planetary degree positions.</p>
              <p><strong>Cosmobiology → Structural Friction.</strong> When three bodies form a midpoint structure (A/B = C), the third body is under tension. Saturn midpoints reveal where fascia is under chronic load. Multiple Saturn midpoints in a session territory = high-priority friction zone.</p>
              <p><strong>Polyvagal → Session Architecture.</strong> The nervous system profile determines pacing, depth, and integration pauses. High dorsal risk requires extreme titration — 5-min work blocks with 2-min integration. High sympathetic requires grounding before upper-body work. Ventral capacity tells you whether the client can accurately report their internal state.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-[16px] p-5">
            <h4 class="font-heading font-bold text-amber-700 mb-2">Important: This Is a Hypothesis, Not a Diagnosis</h4>
            <p class="text-sm text-amber-600 leading-relaxed">The Stars Engine produces <strong>architectural predictions</strong> based on birth chart computation — not clinical assessments. Every prediction should be verified against in-session observation. The body on the table is always the authority; the chart is a working hypothesis. Use the Confirm/Deny buttons to track which predictions match your clinical experience.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Invoicing Panel -->
      <div id="panel-invoicing" class="tab-panel hidden space-y-6">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-2">Billing</p>
          <h1 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-brand-teal">Invoicing</h1>
          <p class="text-sm text-brand-charcoal/60 mt-2">Create and track client invoices. <a href="https://stripe.com" target="_blank" class="text-brand-teal hover:underline">Set up Stripe</a> to accept payments.</p>
        </div>
        <form id="invoice-form" class="bg-white rounded-[20px] border border-brand-teal/10 p-6 shadow-sm space-y-4">
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
            <input type="text" id="inv-client" placeholder="Client name" class="rounded-xl border border-brand-teal/15 px-4 py-3 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:border-brand-teal" />
            <input type="number" id="inv-amount" placeholder="Amount ($)" step="0.01" class="rounded-xl border border-brand-teal/15 px-4 py-3 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:border-brand-teal" />
            <input type="date" id="inv-due" class="rounded-xl border border-brand-teal/15 px-4 py-3 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:border-brand-teal" />
            <select id="inv-status" class="rounded-xl border border-brand-teal/15 px-4 py-3 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:border-brand-teal">
              <option value="draft">Draft</option><option value="sent">Sent</option><option value="paid">Paid</option>
            </select>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <input type="text" id="inv-desc" placeholder="Description (e.g., Session 3 — 10-Series)" class="rounded-xl border border-brand-teal/15 px-4 py-3 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:border-brand-teal" />
            <input type="text" id="inv-link" placeholder="Stripe Payment Link (optional)" class="rounded-xl border border-brand-teal/15 px-4 py-3 text-sm focus:outline-none focus:border-brand-teal" />
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <button type="submit" class="rounded-full bg-brand-teal text-white font-semibold px-6 py-3 text-sm hover:bg-brand-teal-light shadow-sm transition-all">Save Invoice</button>
          </div>
        </form>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4" id="invoice-list"></div>
      </div>
    </main>
    </div><!-- /flex body -->
  </div><!-- /app -->
</body>
</html>

<script>
  const ACCESS_KEY = "cosmic-stars-2026";

  // ── Auth ──
  const authGate = document.getElementById("auth-gate")!;
  const app = document.getElementById("app")!;
  const authInput = document.getElementById("auth-password") as HTMLInputElement;
  const authError = document.getElementById("auth-error")!;

  if (localStorage.getItem("portal-auth") === ACCESS_KEY) {
    authGate.classList.add("hidden");
    app.classList.remove("hidden");
  }
  authInput.addEventListener("keydown", (e) => {
    if (e.key === "Enter") {
      if (authInput.value === ACCESS_KEY) {
        localStorage.setItem("portal-auth", ACCESS_KEY);
        authGate.classList.add("hidden");
        app.classList.remove("hidden");
        authError.classList.add("hidden");
        refreshOverview();
      } else {
        authError.classList.remove("hidden");
        authInput.value = "";
      }
    }
  });
  document.getElementById("logout-btn")?.addEventListener("click", () => {
    localStorage.removeItem("portal-auth");
    location.reload();
  });

  // ── Tab Navigation ──
  document.querySelectorAll(".nav-btn").forEach(btn => {
    btn.addEventListener("click", () => {
      const tabId = (btn as HTMLElement).dataset.tab!;
      switchTab(tabId);
    });
  });
  document.querySelectorAll(".quick-action").forEach(btn => {
    btn.addEventListener("click", () => {
      const tabId = (btn as HTMLElement).dataset.tab!;
      switchTab(tabId);
    });
  });

  function switchTab(tabId: string) {
    document.querySelectorAll(".nav-btn").forEach(b => {
      const isActive = (b as HTMLElement).dataset.tab === tabId;
      b.classList.toggle("bg-white/15", isActive);
      b.classList.toggle("text-white", isActive);
      b.classList.toggle("text-white/60", !isActive);
      b.classList.toggle("hover:text-white", !isActive);
      b.classList.toggle("hover:bg-white/10", !isActive);
    });
    document.querySelectorAll(".tab-panel").forEach(p => {
      p.classList.toggle("hidden", p.id !== `panel-${tabId}`);
    });
    if (tabId === "overview") refreshOverview();
    if (tabId === "clients") renderClients();
    if (tabId === "soap") renderSOAPNotes();
    if (tabId === "calendar") renderCalendar();
    if (tabId === "financial") renderFinancial();
    if (tabId === "invoicing") renderInvoices();
  }

  // ── Storage Helpers ──
  function load(key: string): any[] {
    try { return JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem(`portal-${key}`) || "[]"); } catch { return []; }
  }
  function save(key: string, data: any[]) {
    localStorage.setItem(`portal-${key}`, JSON.stringify(data));
  }

  // ── Overview ──
  function refreshOverview() {
    const clients = load("clients");
    const soap = load("soap");
    const cal = load("calendar");
    const fin = load("financial");
    const now = new Date();
    const thisMonth = fin.filter((t: any) => new Date(t.date).getMonth() === now.getMonth() && t.type === "income").reduce((s: number, t: any) => s + t.amount, 0);
    const ytd = fin.filter((t: any) => new Date(t.date).getFullYear() === now.getFullYear() && t.type === "income").reduce((s: number, t: any) => s + t.amount, 0);
    const nextApt = cal.filter((a: any) => new Date(a.date + "T" + a.time) > now).sort((a: any, b: any) => new Date(a.date + "T" + a.time).getTime() - new Date(b.date + "T" + b.time).getTime())[0];

    document.getElementById("stat-clients")!.textContent = String(clients.length);
    document.getElementById("stat-sessions")!.textContent = String(soap.filter((s: any) => new Date(s.date).getMonth() === now.getMonth()).length);
    document.getElementById("stat-revenue")!.textContent = "$" + thisMonth.toLocaleString();
    document.getElementById("stat-next")!.textContent = nextApt ? `${nextApt.client} — ${nextApt.date}` : "None";

    const recent = [
      ...soap.slice(-3).map((s: any) => ({ type: "SOAP", text: `${s.client} — Session ${s.session} (${s.date})`, date: s.date })),
      ...cal.filter((a: any) => new Date(a.date + "T" + a.time) > now).slice(0, 3).map((a: any) => ({ type: "Appt", text: `${a.client} — ${a.date} ${a.time}`, date: a.date })),
    ].sort((a: any, b: any) => new Date(b.date).getTime() - new Date(a.date).getTime()).slice(0, 5);

    const activityEl = document.getElementById("recent-activity")!;
    activityEl.innerHTML = recent.length ? recent.map(r => `<p class="mb-1"><span class="text-brand-teal font-semibold text-xs">${r.type}</span> ${r.text}</p>`).join("") : "<p class='text-sm text-brand-charcoal/50'>No recent activity</p>";
  }

  // ── SI Predictions ──
  document.getElementById("si-form")!.addEventListener("submit", async (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    const name = (document.getElementById("si-name") as HTMLInputElement).value || "Client";
    const date = (document.getElementById("si-date") as HTMLInputElement).value;
    const time = (document.getElementById("si-time") as HTMLInputElement).value;
    const location = (document.getElementById("si-location") as HTMLInputElement).value;
    const errEl = document.getElementById("si-error")!;
    const submitBtn = document.getElementById("si-submit") as HTMLButtonElement;
    const submitText = document.getElementById("si-submit-text")!;
    const submitSpinner = document.getElementById("si-submit-spinner")!;
    if (!date) { errEl.textContent = "Birth date required"; errEl.classList.remove("hidden"); return; }
    errEl.classList.add("hidden");
    submitBtn.disabled = true;
    submitText.classList.add("hidden");
    submitSpinner.classList.remove("hidden");

    try {
      const resp = await fetch("https://cosmiccalibrations.madmanwithabox.org/api/stars/si-predict", {
        method: "POST", headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
        body: JSON.stringify({ name, birth_date: date, birth_time: time || undefined, birth_location: location || "Austin, TX" }),
      });
      const data = await resp.json();
      if (data.error) { errEl.textContent = data.error; errEl.classList.remove("hidden"); return; }
      renderSIResults(data);
    } catch { errEl.textContent = "Network error"; errEl.classList.remove("hidden"); }
    finally { submitBtn.disabled = false; submitText.classList.remove("hidden"); submitSpinner.classList.add("hidden"); }
  });

  function renderSIResults(data: any) {
    const si = data.structural_integration;
    const el = document.getElementById("si-results")!;
    el.classList.remove("hidden");
    el.innerHTML = `
      <div class="bg-white rounded-[20px] border border-brand-teal/10 p-6 shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-brand-teal text-lg">${data.name}</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-brand-grey">${data.chart_summary.sun_sign} Sun · ${data.chart_summary.moon_sign} Moon · ${data.chart_summary.hd_type} ${data.chart_summary.hd_profile}</p>
            ${data.warning ? `<p class="text-xs text-amber-600 mt-1">${data.warning}</p>` : ""}
          </div>
          <button onclick="window.print()" class="text-xs text-brand-grey hover:text-brand-teal font-medium">Print</button>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-brand-charcoal/70 mb-4">${si.client_summary}</p>
        ${si.contraindications?.length ? `<div class="p-3 rounded-xl bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 mb-4"><p class="text-xs font-bold text-amber-700 mb-1">Contraindications</p>${si.contraindications.map((c: string) => `<p class="text-xs text-amber-600">${c}</p>`).join("")}</div>` : ""}
        <div class="space-y-3">
          ${si.session_plan.map((s: any) => `
            <details class="group">
              <summary class="cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between p-3 rounded-xl bg-brand-paper hover:bg-brand-teal/5 transition-colors">
                <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-brand-teal">${s.session}. ${s.rolfing_focus}</span>
                <span class="text-xs text-brand-grey">${s.armor_priority?.length || 0} armor · ${s.gene_keys_somatic_shadows?.length || 0} shadows</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="mt-2 p-4 space-y-3 text-sm">
                <p><strong class="text-brand-teal">Pacing:</strong> ${s.pacing}</p>
                ${s.armor_priority?.length ? `<div><strong class="text-brand-teal">Armor:</strong> ${s.armor_priority.map((a: any) => `<span class="inline-block text-xs mr-1 mb-1 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full ${a.status.includes('ARMORED') ? 'bg-amber-100 text-amber-700' : 'bg-green-50 text-green-700'}">${a.segment}: ${a.status}</span>`).join(" ")}</div>` : ""}
                ${s.emotional_release_potential ? `<p class="text-brand-charcoal/70 leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-brand-teal">Emotional:</strong> ${s.emotional_release_potential}</p>` : ""}
              </div>
            </details>
          `).join("")}
        </div>
      </div>`;
  }

  // ── Calendar ──
  document.getElementById("cal-add-btn")!.addEventListener("click", () => document.getElementById("cal-form")!.classList.remove("hidden"));
  document.getElementById("cal-cancel")!.addEventListener("click", () => document.getElementById("cal-form")!.classList.add("hidden"));
  document.getElementById("cal-form")!.addEventListener("submit", (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    const cal = load("calendar");
    cal.push({
      client: (document.getElementById("cal-client") as HTMLInputElement).value,
      date: (document.getElementById("cal-date") as HTMLInputElement).value,
      time: (document.getElementById("cal-time") as HTMLInputElement).value,
    });
    cal.sort((a: any, b: any) => new Date(a.date + "T" + a.time).getTime() - new Date(b.date + "T" + b.time).getTime());
    save("calendar", cal);
    (document.getElementById("cal-form") as HTMLFormElement).reset();
    document.getElementById("cal-form")!.classList.add("hidden");
    renderCalendar();
  });

  function renderCalendar() {
    const cal = load("calendar");
    const now = new Date();
    const upcoming = cal.filter((a: any) => new Date(a.date + "T" + a.time) > now);
    const el = document.getElementById("calendar-list")!;
    el.innerHTML = upcoming.length ? upcoming.map((a: any) => `
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between p-3 rounded-xl bg-brand-paper">
        <div><span class="text-sm font-semibold text-brand-charcoal">${a.client}</span><span class="text-xs text-brand-grey ml-2">${a.date} at ${a.time}</span></div>
        <button class="text-xs text-red-400 hover:text-red-600" onclick="event.stopPropagation();const c=JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('portal-calendar')||'[]');const i=c.findIndex((x:any)=>x.client==='${a.client}'&&x.date==='${a.date}');if(i>-1){c.splice(i,1);localStorage.setItem('portal-calendar',JSON.stringify(c));renderCalendar();}">Remove</button>
      </div>`).join("") : "<p class='text-sm text-brand-charcoal/40'>No upcoming appointments.</p>";
  }

  // ── SOAP Notes ──
  document.getElementById("soap-form")!.addEventListener("submit", (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    const soap = load("soap");
    soap.unshift({
      client: (document.getElementById("soap-client") as HTMLInputElement).value,
      date: (document.getElementById("soap-date") as HTMLInputElement).value,
      session: (document.getElementById("soap-session") as HTMLInputElement).value,
      subjective: (document.getElementById("soap-subjective") as HTMLTextAreaElement).value,
      objective: (document.getElementById("soap-objective") as HTMLTextAreaElement).value,
      assessment: (document.getElementById("soap-assessment") as HTMLTextAreaElement).value,
      plan: (document.getElementById("soap-plan") as HTMLTextAreaElement).value,
    });
    save("soap", soap);
    (document.getElementById("soap-form") as HTMLFormElement).reset();
    renderSOAPNotes();
    refreshOverview();
  });

  function renderSOAPNotes() {
    const soap = load("soap");
    const el = document.getElementById("soap-list")!;
    el.innerHTML = soap.length ? soap.map((s: any, i: number) => `
      <details class="bg-white rounded-[20px] border border-brand-teal/10 p-6 shadow-sm">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between">
          <div><span class="font-semibold text-brand-teal">${s.client}</span><span class="text-xs text-brand-grey ml-3">Session ${s.session} — ${s.date}</span></div>
          <button class="text-xs text-red-400 hover:text-red-600" onclick="event.preventDefault();event.stopPropagation();const so=JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('portal-soap')||'[]');so.splice(${i},1);localStorage.setItem('portal-soap',JSON.stringify(so));renderSOAPNotes();refreshOverview();">Delete</button>
        </summary>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm">
          ${["Subjective","Objective","Assessment","Plan"].map(f => `<div><p class="text-xs font-bold text-brand-grey uppercase mb-1">${f}</p><p class="text-brand-charcoal/70">${s[f.toLowerCase()] || "—"}</p></div>`).join("")}
        </div>
      </details>`).join("") : "<p class='text-sm text-brand-charcoal/40'>No SOAP notes yet.</p>";
  }

  document.getElementById("soap-export")!.addEventListener("click", () => {
    const soap = load("soap");
    const text = soap.map((s: any) => `CLIENT: ${s.client} | Session ${s.session} | ${s.date}\nS: ${s.subjective}\nO: ${s.objective}\nA: ${s.assessment}\nP: ${s.plan}\n---\n`).join("\n");
    const blob = new Blob([text], { type: "text/plain" });
    const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
    const a = document.createElement("a");
    a.href = url; a.download = "soap-notes-export.txt"; a.click();
  });

  // ── Clients ──
  document.getElementById("client-add-btn")!.addEventListener("click", () => document.getElementById("client-form")!.classList.toggle("hidden"));
  document.getElementById("client-cancel")!.addEventListener("click", () => document.getElementById("client-form")!.classList.add("hidden"));
  document.getElementById("client-form")!.addEventListener("submit", async (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    const btn = (e.target as HTMLFormElement).querySelector("button[type=submit]") as HTMLButtonElement;
    const origText = btn.textContent;
    btn.textContent = "Generating SI guide...";
    btn.disabled = true;

    const name = (document.getElementById("client-name") as HTMLInputElement).value;
    const birthDate = (document.getElementById("client-birth-date") as HTMLInputElement).value;
    const birthTime = (document.getElementById("client-birth-time") as HTMLInputElement).value;
    const birthLocation = (document.getElementById("client-birth-location") as HTMLInputElement).value;

    let siGuide = null;
    if (birthDate) {
      try {
        const resp = await fetch("https://cosmiccalibrations.madmanwithabox.org/api/stars/si-predict", {
          method: "POST", headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
          body: JSON.stringify({ name, birth_date: birthDate, birth_time: birthTime || undefined, birth_location: birthLocation || "Austin, TX" }),
        });
        const data = await resp.json();
        if (!data.error) siGuide = data.structural_integration;
      } catch {}
    }

    const clients = load("clients");
    clients.push({
      name,
      email: (document.getElementById("client-email") as HTMLInputElement).value,
      phone: (document.getElementById("client-phone") as HTMLInputElement).value,
      birthDate, birthTime, birthLocation,
      notes: (document.getElementById("client-notes") as HTMLTextAreaElement).value,
      siGuide,
      created: new Date().toISOString().split("T")[0],
    });
    save("clients", clients);
    (document.getElementById("client-form") as HTMLFormElement).reset();
    document.getElementById("client-form")!.classList.add("hidden");
    btn.textContent = origText;
    btn.disabled = false;
    renderClients();
    refreshOverview();
  });

  function renderClients() {
    const clients = load("clients");
    const el = document.getElementById("client-list")!;
    el.innerHTML = clients.length ? clients.map((c: any, i: number) => `
